    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Barrow-Draugr are undead warriors that rise from the burial mounds of the Ashen Woods. Clad in corroded iron and bearing rusted blades, they fight with the brutal determination of their living days. Their wounds fester with poison, and their cold grip drains the warmth from the living.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Barrow-Draugr are straightforward melee brutes. Lead with Rusted Blade for poison damage, then use Death Grip to lock down a target. Keep them near open barrows when possible — Grave-Bound gives them 5 regen per turn. Focus fire on the PC who deals fire damage, as they take double from fire. Pair with Grave-Singers who can raise them if they fall.</p>",
